From: Chris Lu <chris.lu@mediatek.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Sep 2024 16:47:02 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: btusb: mediatek: move Bluetooth power off command
 position
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.12.8
Git-commit: ad0c6f603bb0b07846fda484c59a176a8cd02838

commit ad0c6f603bb0b07846fda484c59a176a8cd02838 upstream.

Move MediaTek Bluetooth power off command before releasing
usb ISO interface.

Signed-off-by: Chris Lu <chris.lu@mediatek.com>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Cc: Fedor Pchelkin <boddah8794@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c b/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
index 11755cb1eb16..b39e10b9addd 100644
--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
@@ -2734,11 +2734,14 @@ static int btusb_mtk_shutdown(struct hci_dev *hdev)
 {
 	struct btusb_data *data = hci_get_drvdata(hdev);
 	struct btmtk_data *btmtk_data = hci_get_priv(hdev);
+	int ret;
+
+	ret = btmtk_usb_shutdown(hdev);
 
 	if (test_bit(BTMTK_ISOPKT_RUNNING, &btmtk_data->flags))
 		btusb_mtk_release_iso_intf(data);
 
-	return btmtk_usb_shutdown(hdev);
+	return ret;
 }
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_PM
